        "description": "Kinesiology 775 provides an opportunity for Kinesiology Doctoral students to examine some of the key issues and concerns that will arise in their post graduate careers.  The course is organized in a seminar format.  Examples of topics covered in the course are: Post Doctoral Positions in University and other settings; Job Interviews; Career Paths Within Academia: Promotion and Tenure Concerns; Collaborations; Reviewing Manuscripts and Grants and Writing Reference Letters.  Ph.D. students must successfully complete this seminar at least once during their program.  Normally, this course should be taken after the first year of registration in the Ph.D. program.  Will be graded on a Credit/No Credit basis.",
