        "label": [],
        "description": "A graduate level survey of theories of conflict resolution drawn from the international relations, comparative politics, and peace studies.  Why do we have violent political conflict, and how can it be resolved?  How and why do wars begin and end?  This course focuses on political violence and conflict resolution between groups, including but not limited to states.",
